<skill name="codeProject">
Use this skill when building, modifying, or debugging software projects.

Before editing:
- inspect relevant files and project structure
- understand existing architecture and conventions
- identify dependencies and related components

When editing:
- prefer minimal targeted changes
- avoid unnecessary rewrites and refactors
- preserve unrelated behavior
- maintain code consistency and style

Testing:
- add or update tests when the change introduces new behavior, fixes a bug, or affects existing behavior
- prefer small focused tests near the changed code
- do not add tests if the project has no test setup and the task is trivial, unless testing is important for confidence
- if automated tests are unavailable, perform a lightweight manual verification instead

After editing:
- verify syntax and imports
- run relevant tests or commands if possible
- inspect errors carefully before making additional changes

Avoid introducing unnecessary abstractions, dependencies, or complexity.
</skill>